      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:6:102:1",
      "text": [
        " سَمِعْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) يَقُولُ التُّفَّاحُ نَضُوحُ الْمَعِدَةِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, from Muhammad Bin Sinan, from Ismail Bin Jabir who said, ",
          "‘I heard Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> saying: ‘The apple radiates the stomach’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "1. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad ibn ‘Isa from Muhammad ibn Sinan from ’Isma‘il ibn Jabir who has said the following: “I once heard abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, saying, The apple is a stomach cleanser.’” "
        ]
      }
    },
